Private Equity / Apex Capital Hub â€“ Key Terms (Chat Version)

LP â€“ Limited Partner
Investors who provide capital to the fund. They have limited liability and do not manage the fund.

GP â€“ General Partner
The fund manager responsible for investment decisions, operations, and performance.

Fund
The investment vehicle that pools capital from LPs to invest in portfolio companies.

Commitment
The total amount an LP agrees to invest in a fund (not paid upfront).

Capital Call (Drawdown)
A request sent by the GP asking LPs to contribute a portion of their committed capital.

Unfunded Commitment
The remaining amount of an LPâ€™s commitment that has not yet been called.

Investment
A deployment of fund capital into a portfolio company.

Valuation
The assessed fair value of an investment at a specific point in time.

NAV â€“ Net Asset Value
Total value of fund assets minus liabilities.

Distribution
Money returned to LPs from investment profits or return of capital.

Waterfall
The rules that define how distributions are split between LPs and the GP.

Preferred Return (Hurdle Rate)
Minimum return (e.g., 8%) that LPs must receive before the GP earns carry.

Carried Interest (Carry)
The GPâ€™s share of profits, typically 20%, after LPs receive preferred returns.

Catch-Up
A phase where the GP receives most or all profits until their carried interest percentage is met.

TVPI â€“ Total Value to Paid-In
(Total Distributions + NAV) Ã· Paid-In Capital

DPI â€“ Distributions to Paid-In
Distributions Ã· Paid-In Capital

RVPI â€“ Residual Value to Paid-In
NAV Ã· Paid-In Capital

IRR â€“ Internal Rate of Return
Annualized rate of return considering timing of cash flows.


